title: Airport Security System Glitch Causes Delays
text:
Airport Security System Glitch Causes Delays October 15, 2015 
U.S. Customs and Border Protection computers that screen passengers against the terror watchlist went down for 90 minutes last night, slowing international passengers trying to check in or out and causing long delays at airports nationwide. 
Department of Homeland Security officials said the system experienced a temporary router outage, which it does not believe to be “malicious in nature.” 0
